  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Territorial Climate Fund for forest people of Mesoamerica</narrative>
  </title>
  <description akvo:type="4" type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable Financing for Forest Governance</narrative>
  </description>
  <description akvo:type="5" type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project focuses on indigenous and forest communities of the Mesoamerican region to have a diagnosis of current financial mechanisms that provides the information needed to design a Mesoamerican Territorial Fund to support low carbon livelihoods and mainly directed to mitigation and adaptation to change climate from the perspective of territorial rights, territorial autonomy and collectivism.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description akvo:type="6" type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This self-managed project will provide co-financing for a Project supported by PORTICUS (DP 00654) directed to take initial steps so that AMPB (Mesoamerican Alliance of Forests People) can strengthen its case to access climate finances from the global environmental and climate benefits. 

Those environmental services originate from sustainable livelihoods of indigenous groups and forest peoples that together represent over 50 million hectares of tropical forests in Mesoamerica.The Construction of the Mesoamerican Territorial Fund (MTF) will be developed in 4 phases:

1. Regional Workshop on Territorial Funds. With different territorial groups , territorial authorities and experts climate in order to make a thorough analysis of such financial instruments and explain their operating funds. (October 2015) Co Financing of PRISMA.

2. Study-diagnosis. Elements on climate and / or territorial funds operated on a global and regional level. 

Of the different models studied, the project will deliver initial recommendation of the features that should have the MTF appropriate to the conditions of the Mesoamerican region and its needs.</narrative>
  </description>
